Surprised by all the good reviews. Following those I decided to try this ramen place. I had the miso ramen. Pretty disappointed with the quality. This is cheap food, in both price and quality. The broth was just salty, no much flavor. The pork was chewy and low quality, couldn't eat it. The egg was the only decent thing and that's the only reason I give 2 stars instead of 1. There are much better ramen places in Brooklyn, but maybe not this cheap. I guess you get what you pay for.

Not only is Naruto a popular anime, but it is also the best ramen shop in Park Slope. Seems like a new one is opening ever week in the neighborhood, but this should be your go to place. Though you are here for the noodles, the fried rice is some of the best around. The only downside, in a cashless society, they are a cash only establishment.

Sadly, I was too hungry to take a photo of my appetizer or ramen but oh my goodness, every bite was so delicious. I had one of the newer, featured ramen bowls called the Cilantro Bomb. It is supposed to come with chicken and shrimp. They were out of chicken for the night so, they stated that they would add extra chicken. Unfortunately, I only had two very small pieces of chicken in my ramen. That's the only thing that cost them a star. The food was delicious, including our steamed pork dumplings which were so soft they were falling apart in our chopsticks. They tasted super fresh and left us wanting. The drink selection is great. They serve Sapporo on tap, have Ramune drinks and other cool traditional drinks. Seating is a little tricky. The long bar in the front (where we sat) did have hooks for coats along the wall and hooks for bags beneath the bar, which was great. However, the draft that was coming in made it pretty uncomfortable. There are tables in the back of the restaurant, it just happened to be a little busier than we expected. The staff were all super friendly, seemed genuinely happy to be at work and were all on their A game. We will definitely be visiting again.
